    "notes": "K0V (Houk & Smith-Moore 1988) sitting just at the G8V/K0V boundary; modern Teff scales (Tanner 2019 5402 K, Brewer 2016 5410 K, Tsantaki 2013 5391 K) all cluster within 20 K of the K0V/G8V transition near 5400 K, with the spectral-type letter assignment depending on which calibration the catalog uses. No direct interferometric angular diameter exists — HD 69830 was not included in Boyajian 2012 CHARA Sun-like-star survey nor in any VLTI-PIONIER programme through 2026. No published asteroseismology either (predicted nu_max ~ 3000 uHz peaks too high for TESS short-cadence and HD 69830 has not been a CHEOPS target). Mass and radius therefore both anchored on Tanner 2019 isochrone + bolometric-flux Stefan-Boltzmann (0.863 +/- 0.043 Msun, 0.905 +/- 0.019 Rsun), with Lovis 2006 (0.86 +/- 0.03 Msun) and Rosenthal 2021 (0.887 +/- 0.019 Rsun) kept as cross-check alternates. Age has a wide literature spread: Mamajek 2008 gyrochronology gives 5.7 +/- 1 Gyr (recommended), Lovis 2006 isochrone gives 4-10 Gyr broad range, Tanner 2019 isochrone gives 10.6 +/- 2 Gyr — Tanner 2019 hits the upper-main-sequence subgiant turnoff degeneracy at this Teff and metallicity, so the gyrochronological 5.7 Gyr is adopted (more reliable diagnostic for an inactive late-G/early-K dwarf at this metallicity). Rotation period 35.5 +/- 0.5 d (Suarez Mascareno 2015) is the only direct P_rot measurement, from Ca II H&K chromospheric activity rotational modulation in long-term HARPS time series; Mamajek 2008 gyrochronology gives 34 +/- 3 d, consistent. Activity log R'HK = -4.95 +/- 0.04 (Gomes da Silva 2021, 240-spectrum HARPS weighted mean) supersedes Henry 1996 Mt Wilson single-snapshot -5.00; Phase 3 markdown currently quotes -5.0 colloquially and should track -4.95. Disk measurements (Beichman 2005 warm dust at ~1 AU, Smith-Wyatt-Haniff 2009 MIDI/VLTI refit, Lisse 2007 composition model, Wyatt 2007 steady-state limit) are stored separately in db/disks_curated.json per the disk-meta migration."
